Spread 2 tablespoons cream cheese on half of one tortilla. Top cheese with 1/4 cup fruit. Fold tortilla in half, enclosing filling. Repeat. Melt half of the butter in nonstick skillet over medium heat. Cook, 2 quesadillas at a time, 4 to 5 minutes, turning once. Remove quesadillas to cutting board; keep warm. Add remaining butter to skillet and cook remaining quesadillas. Meanwhile, heat dessert sauce in microwavable dish for 10 seconds or until warm enough to pour. Cut each quesadilla into 4 wedges and arrange on serving plates. Drizzle with sauce and sprinkle with almonds.